30/11/2005
SARAJEVO, Bosnia and Herzegovina (BiH) -- Opening a conference titled "Dayton - Ten Years After", Slovenian Foreign Minister and OSCE Chairman-in-Office Dimitrij Rupel said Tuesday (29 November) that preparing for EU integration would be the biggest challenge faced by BiH and international authorities in the near future. 
He said the launch of negotiations on a Stabilisation and Association Agreement represents a new start for BiH, adding that the process of European integrations is a long one and requires difficult political decisions.
In other news Tuesday, the first contingent of BiH's mine removing unit returned from Iraq. 
Poor weather forced the second contingent to delay its departure to Iraq until Wednesday.
Also Tuesday, Brigadier General Vincenzo Coppola was appointed new head of the European Union Police Mission. 
He replaces outgoing chief Kevin Carty in January. 
(Dnevni Avaz, Nezavisne Novine - 30/11/05; PBS BiH, Fena, RTRS, EUPM Web site - 29/11/05; EU Web site - 28/11/05)
